---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Travel & Transport" description="Complete guide to reaching Gurugram and getting around the city.">
  <Hero 
    title="Travel & Transport"
    subtitle="Your Guide to Getting Around"
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 3rem;">
        <h2>How to Reach Gurugram</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); font-size: 1.1rem; max-width: 700px; margin: 1rem auto;">
          Gurugram is well-connected by air, rail, and road, making it easily accessible from anywhere in India and abroad.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-3" style="margin-bottom: 4rem;">
        <div class="card" style="padding: 2rem; text-align: center;">
          <div style="font-size: 3rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">‚úàÔ∏è</div>
          <h3>By Air</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin: 1rem 0;">
            <strong>Indira Gandhi International Airport (DEL)</strong><br/>
            Distance: 15 km from Gurugram<br/>
            Travel Time: 30-45 minutes
          </p>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); font-size: 0.9rem; margin-top: 1rem;">
            The airport is well-connected to major cities worldwide. From the airport, you can take:
          </p>
          <ul style="color: var(--color-text-light); line-height: 2; margin-top: 1rem; text-align: left; font-size: 0.9rem;">
            <li>‚Ä¢ Airport Taxi/Cab (‚Çπ500-800)</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Metro (Yellow Line to HUDA City Centre)</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Airport Express Bus</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="card" style="padding: 2rem; text-align: center;">
          <div style="font-size: 3rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">üöÇ</div>
          <h3>By Train</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin: 1rem 0;">
            <strong>Gurugram Railway Station</strong><br/>
            Connects to major cities in India
          </p>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); font-size: 0.9rem; margin-top: 1rem;">
            Alternative stations nearby:
          </p>
          <ul style="color: var(--color-text-light); line-height: 2; margin-top: 1rem; text-align: left; font-size: 0.9rem;">
            <li>‚Ä¢ New Delhi Railway Station (30 km)</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Nizamuddin Railway Station (35 km)</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Hazrat Nizamuddin (35 km)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="card" style="padding: 2rem; text-align: center;">
          <div style="font-size: 3rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">üöó</div>
          <h3>By Road</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin: 1rem 0;">
            <strong>Well-Connected via Highways</strong><br/>
            NH-8 and NH-48 pass through Gurugram
          </p>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); font-size: 0.9rem; margin-top: 1rem;">
            Road connections:
          </p>
          <ul style="color: var(--color-text-light); line-height: 2; margin-top: 1rem; text-align: left; font-size: 0.9rem;">
            <li>‚Ä¢ Delhi: 30 km (1 hour)</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Jaipur: 250 km (4 hours)</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Agra: 200 km (3.5 hours)</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Regular bus services available</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 style="text-align: center; margin: 4rem 0 3rem;">Local Transport</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-2">
        <div class="card" style="padding: 2rem;">
          <h3>Metro</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin-bottom: 1rem;">
            The Rapid Metro connects various parts of Gurugram and links to the Delhi Metro network.
          </p>
          <ul style="color: var(--color-text-light); line-height: 2;">
            <li><strong>Rapid Metro:</strong> Connects Cyber City, Sector 55-56, and other areas</li>
            <li><strong>Delhi Metro:</strong> Yellow Line extends to HUDA City Centre</li>
            <li><strong>Fare:</strong> ‚Çπ10-50 depending on distance</li>
            <li><strong>Timings:</strong> 6:00 AM - 11:00 PM</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="card" style="padding: 2rem;">
          <h3>Buses</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin-bottom: 1rem;">
            Haryana Roadways and private operators provide bus services within the city and to nearby areas.
          </p>
          <ul style="color: var(--color-text-light); line-height: 2;">
            <li><strong>City Buses:</strong> Regular services across Gurugram</li>
            <li><strong>Intercity:</strong> Connections to Delhi, Faridabad, and other cities</li>
            <li><strong>Fare:</strong> ‚Çπ10-100 depending on distance</li>
            <li><strong>Frequency:</strong> Every 10-15 minutes on major routes</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="card" style="padding: 2rem;">
          <h3>Taxis & Cabs</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin-bottom: 1rem;">
            Multiple cab services operate in Gurugram for convenient point-to-point travel.
          </p>
          <ul style="color: var(--color-text-light); line-height: 2;">
            <li><strong>App-based:</strong> Uber, Ola, Rapido</li>
            <li><strong>Auto-rickshaws:</strong> Available throughout the city</li>
            <li><strong>Taxi Services:</strong> Pre-paid and on-demand</li>
            <li><strong>Fare:</strong> Varies by service and distance</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="card" style="padding: 2rem;">
          <h3>Car Rental</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin-bottom: 1rem;">
            Self-drive and chauffeur-driven car rental options are available for flexible travel.
          </p>
          <ul style="color: var(--color-text-light); line-height: 2;">
            <li><strong>Self-drive:</strong> Zoomcar, Revv, Myles</li>
            <li><strong>Chauffeur-driven:</strong> Various rental companies</li>
            <li><strong>Rates:</strong> Starting from ‚Çπ1,500/day</li>
            <li><strong>Booking:</strong> Online and offline options</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card" style="padding: 2rem; background: var(--color-bg-light); margin-top: 3rem;">
        <h3 style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Transport Tips</h3>
        <div class="grid grid-2">
          <ul style="color: var(--color-text-light); line-height: 2;">
            <li>‚úì Metro is the fastest way to travel during peak hours</li>
            <li>‚úì Use app-based cabs for convenience and safety</li>
            <li>‚úì Auto-rickshaws are economical for short distances</li>
            <li>‚úì Book airport transfers in advance</li>
          </ul>
          <ul style="color: var(--color-text-light); line-height: 2;">
            <li>‚úì Traffic can be heavy during office hours (9 AM - 6 PM)</li>
            <li>‚úì Keep cash for auto-rickshaws and local buses</li>
            <li>‚úì Download metro apps for route planning</li>
            <li>‚úì Consider car rental for day trips</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>


